@alexgorbachev tweeted me recently after picking up my presentation on Performance Testing and OBIEE. His question got me thinking, and as ever the answer &ldquo;It Depends&rdquo; is appropriate here :-)
Why is the measurement being done? Without knowing the context of the work Alex is doing, how to measure depends on whether the measurement needs to be of: -
The actual response times that the users are getting, or The response times that the system is currently capable of delivering This may sound like splitting hairs or beard-scratching irrelevance, but it&rsquo;s not.

I posted a while ago about the sawserver (Presentation Services) log configuration file. Today I&rsquo;m doing some work digging around why sawserver&rsquo;s throwing an error and so increased the log detail. This parameter is really helpful to use:
fmtName=&ldquo;short&rdquo;
Consider in these two screenshots, the first is with the default log format and shows about six entries. The second is short log format and is about ten times as much data.
